                            <comment id="13682641" author="bitstorm" created="Thu, 13 Jun 2013 20:02:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve attached a quickstart project as well to show you the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13683187" author="mgrigorov" created="Fri, 14 Jun 2013 08:13:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The suggested patch is not good because the prepended/appended scripts by AjaxRequestTarget may need JS library to be able to do their job.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13683201" author="mgrigorov" created="Fri, 14 Jun 2013 08:24:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;AjaxHeaderResponse now handles OnEventHeaderItem specially as it already does with OnLoad and OnDomReady header items&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13691237" author="bitstorm" created="Sat, 22 Jun 2013 20:12:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Method getJavaScript of OnEventHeaderItem returns the script without its event handler. I added a patch that adds method getFullJavaScript to OnEventHeaderItem to solve the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
